## Code Conventions

### Naming
- **Components**: PascalCase (`PokerTable.tsx`)
- **Utilities**: camelCase (`hand-notation.ts`, `formatMoney()`)
- **Types**: PascalCase (`GameState`, `Player`)
- **Constants**: UPPER_SNAKE_CASE (`VARIANCE_RATE`, `SMALL_BLIND`)
- **Store actions**: camelCase (`startHand()`, `playerAction()`)

### File Organization
- One component per file
- Co-locate types with implementation when domain-specific
- Shared types in `types/poker.ts`
- Tests in `__tests__/` sibling folder

### TypeScript
- **Strict mode** enabled
- Prefer type inference over explicit annotations
- Use template literal types for card notation
- Avoid `any` (use `unknown` if needed)

### React
- Functional components only (no classes)
- Hooks at top level (never in conditionals)
- `useGameStore()` for state, avoid prop drilling
- `useGameStore.getState()` in handlers to avoid stale closures
- Key props on lists (use stable IDs, not indices)

### Styling
- Tailwind utility classes (avoid inline styles)
- Dark mode variants via `dark:` prefix
- Mobile-first responsive design
- Use `dvh` for viewport height (not `vh`)
- Touch-friendly tap targets (min 44x44px)

---

## Performance Considerations

- **Lazy loading**: Stats + Review tabs only load on first view
- **Web Worker**: EV simulation off main thread (2000 Monte Carlo runs)
- **Debounced actions**: AI think delays prevent UI lock
- **Indexed state**: `currentPlayerIndex`, `dealerIndex` for O(1) lookups
- **Vite chunking**: Recharts in separate chunk (manual splitChunks)
- **Progressive board reveal**: `visibleBoardCount` state for staggered animations
- **IndexedDB**: Offloads hand history from memory after session

---

## Security & Privacy

- **Fully client-side**: No data sent to external servers
- **No auth**: No user accounts or personal data collected
- **Local storage only**: Theme + settings in localStorage
- **IndexedDB**: Hand history stays on device
- **No analytics**: No tracking or telemetry
- **No external CDN**: All assets bundled (GTO JSON served from `/public`)

